#Fixing openshift SSL 

Namecheap (Registrar)
        ↓
Route53 (DNS - ACTIVE)
        ↓                -> Lets Encrypt
OpenShift Ingress (AWS ELB)
        ↓
Routes (console + oauth)


sudo certbot certonly   --manual   --preferred-challenges dns   -d "*.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online"   -d "apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online"
Go to Route 53 -> create a method -> TXT -> Add the key and the value generated by the above command
sudo cp /etc/letsencrypt/live/apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online/fullchain.pem /etc/letsencrypt/live/apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online/privkey.pem /tmp/
oc create secret tls letsencrypt-wildcard-apps   --cert=/tmp/fullchain.pem   --key=/tmp/privkey.pem   -n openshift-ingress

cat ingress-cert-patch.yaml
apiVersion: operator.openshift.io/v1
kind: IngressController
metadata:
  name: default
  namespace: openshift-ingress-operator
spec:
  defaultCertificate:
    name: letsencrypt-wildcard-apps
EOF

cat apiserver-cert-patch.yaml
apiVersion: config.openshift.io/v1
kind: APIServer
metadata:
  name: cluster
spec:
  servingCerts:
    namedCertificates:
    - names:
      - api.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online
      servingCertificate:
        name: api-named-cert
EOF

oc apply -f ingress-cert-patch.yaml
oc apply -f apiserver-cert-patch.yaml
oc get ingresscontroller -n openshift-ingress-operator default -o yaml | grep -A5 defaultCertificate
oc get apiserver cluster -o yaml | grep -A10 servingCerts


oc get pods -n openshift-ingress


Lab 1: TLS Route (External Traffic)

#delete: oc delete all -l app=frontend

Step 1: Create project
oc new-project bank-app-tls
Verify
oc project
oc get all
Step 2: Deploy apps
oc new-app --docker-image=35.153.133.45:5000/nginx --name=frontend
oc new-app --docker-image=35.153.133.45:5000/nginx --name=backend
oc new-app --docker-image=35.153.133.45:5000/nginx --name=database

Verify
oc get pods
oc get svc
oc get deploy

Wait until all are running:

oc get pods -w
Step 3: Expose frontend with Route
oc expose svc frontend
Verify
oc get route

You will get a host similar to:

frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online
Step 4: Enable TLS edge termination on the route

Run:

oc patch route frontend -p '{"spec":{"tls":{"termination":"edge","insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy":"Redirect"}}}'
What this does
enables HTTPS on the route
router handles the certificate
HTTP requests get redirected to HTTPS
Step 5: Verify the route configuration
oc get route frontend -o yaml

You should see:

tls:
  termination: edge
  insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy: Redirect
Step 6: Browse the frontend in different ways
Way 1: Browser

Open:

https://frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online

You should see the nginx page over HTTPS.

Way 2: curl HTTPS
curl -I https://frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online

You should see HTTP/1.1 200 OK.

Way 3: test HTTP redirect
curl -I http://frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online

You should see a redirect because of:

insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy: Redirect
Way 4: OpenShift console
Developer view
project bank-app-tls
Topology
click frontend
click route URL
Step 7: Explain edge termination clearly

Use this in class:

Browser --HTTPS--> OpenShift Router --HTTP--> Frontend Pod

So:

external traffic is encrypted
internal traffic from router to pod is not encrypted in edge mode

That is the key teaching point.

Step 8: Test internal communication before policies

By default everything is open.

Frontend to backend
oc exec deploy/frontend -- curl -s backend
Backend to database
oc exec deploy/backend -- curl -s database
Frontend to database
oc exec deploy/frontend -- curl -s database

All should work initially.

Step 9: Apply deny-all ingress policy

Create deny-all-ingress.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: deny-all-ingress
spec:
  podSelector: {}
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress

Apply it:

oc apply -f deny-all-ingress.yaml
Step 10: Test again after deny-all
Internal tests
oc exec deploy/frontend -- curl --max-time 5 backend
oc exec deploy/backend -- curl --max-time 5 database

These should fail.

External route

Now test the frontend route again:

curl -k -I https://frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online

Depending on how traffic reaches the pod, frontend may also become inaccessible because all ingress to the frontend pod is blocked.

This is a good point to explain that Route gives exposure, but NetworkPolicy still controls whether traffic can enter the pod.

Step 11: Allow traffic to frontend

Create allow-to-frontend.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-to-frontend
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      app: frontend
  ingress:
  - {}
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress

Apply:

oc apply -f allow-to-frontend.yaml
Test browser again
curl -I https://frontend-bank-app-tls.apps.venky-ocp.beyondcloud.online

And open it in browser again.

Now frontend should be reachable over HTTPS again.

Step 12: Allow frontend to backend

Create allow-frontend-to-backend.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-frontend-to-backend
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      app: backend
  ingress:
  - from:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: frontend
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress

Apply:

oc apply -f allow-frontend-to-backend.yaml
Test
oc exec deploy/frontend -- curl -s backend

Should work.

Negative test
oc exec deploy/database -- curl --max-time 5 backend

Should fail.

Step 13: Allow backend to database

Create allow-backend-to-db.yaml:

apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: NetworkPolicy
metadata:
  name: allow-backend-to-db
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      app: database
  ingress:
  - from:
    - podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          app: backend
  policyTypes:
  - Ingress

Apply:

oc apply -f allow-backend-to-db.yaml
Test success
oc exec deploy/backend -- curl -s database
Test failure
oc exec deploy/frontend -- curl --max-time 5 database

Should fail.

Step 14: Final architecture to explain
User --HTTPS--> Route/Router --HTTP--> Frontend
Frontend ---------> Backend
Backend ----------> Database
Frontend -X-> Database
Other traffic blocked
